1
00:00:01,890 --> 00:00:03,750
Instructor: Button that I want to work on

2
00:00:03,750 --> 00:00:06,000
is Cancel Order.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,960
So let me go back here actually to the orders.

4
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:13,470
And if we have something that is approved here.

5
00:00:13,470 --> 00:00:15,600
This is a customer order.

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:20,190
So if we cancel the order, we want to update the status.

7
00:00:20,190 --> 00:00:23,910
But on top of that, I want to show you one more thing.

8
00:00:23,910 --> 00:00:27,780
We actually want to give a refund to this customer,

9
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:30,720
and we have the Payment Intent ID.

10
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:35,553
Based on that, we can use Stripe to easily give refund.

11
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:38,580
Let me show that.

12
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:42,000
We will go back here in the Details,

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,103
where we have the Cancel Order.

14
00:00:44,940 --> 00:00:48,333
Let me add an asp-action of CancelOrder.

15
00:00:50,610 --> 00:00:54,243
Copy that, and we will create an action method.

16
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:58,710
Let me copy this action method for ShipOrder,

17
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:01,620
paste it here with the closing bracket,

18
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:04,903
and I will copy the action name CancelOrder.

19
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:07,973
Perfect.

20
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:12,480
When we have to cancel the order,

21
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:16,320
first we will retrieve that order from database.

22
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,780
And then, inside orderHeader,

23
00:01:18,780 --> 00:01:21,510
we can check the PaymentStatus.

24
00:01:21,510 --> 00:01:26,193
If PaymentStatus==SD.PaymentStatusApproved,

25
00:01:27,330 --> 00:01:30,150
that means payment was already done

26
00:01:30,150 --> 00:01:32,313
and we have to give them a refund.

27
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:35,910
Now in order to give them a refund,

28
00:01:35,910 --> 00:01:38,640
we will create a variable options

29
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:42,450
of new RefundCreateOptions.

30
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:45,873
And you can see that is inside the Stripe class.

31
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:48,900
That looks good.

32
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,900
Inside there, you can give some Reason,

33
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:55,580
like RefundReasons.RequestedByCustomer.

34
00:01:57,150 --> 00:02:00,900
And you have to provide the Payment Intent ID

35
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:04,337
that is inside orderHeader.PaymentIntentId.

36
00:02:06,570 --> 00:02:08,340
Once you have the option,

37
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:11,520
then again we have to create a service.

38
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:14,670
But this time, it will be a RefundService,

39
00:02:14,670 --> 00:02:17,040
which is inside Stripe.

40
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:20,564
And then, we will get a refund object

41
00:02:20,564 --> 00:02:25,564
by calling the service.Create with the options.

42
00:02:26,970 --> 00:02:28,890
Simple as that.

43
00:02:28,890 --> 00:02:31,560
With that, the refund has been processed.

44
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:35,070
And if you want, you can also log the refund status

45
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:39,753
or the refund ID in your database by creating a new field.

46
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:42,690
What I will do is right here,

47
00:02:42,690 --> 00:02:46,667
I will update unitOfWork.OrderHeader.UpdateStatus.

48
00:02:49,290 --> 00:02:53,310
Change that to be orderHeader.Id.

49
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:57,330
The ID is inside orderHeader.Id.

50
00:02:57,330 --> 00:03:00,900
And the status will be StatusCancelled.

51
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:04,653
Payment status will be SD.StatusRefunded.

52
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:09,360
In the else part here,

53
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:12,480
we are not going to give them any refund,

54
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:15,453
so we will directly say StatusCancelled.

55
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,750
Finally, we have to save the changes,

56
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:21,930
so let me copy that from the top here,

57
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:23,640
paste it here,

58
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:27,540
and I will say, "Order Cancelled Successfully."

59
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:28,773
Redirect back.

60
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,580
Perfect. That looks good.

61
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:36,273
Let me save this and restart the application.

62
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:39,810
We are logged in as the admin here.

63
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:42,600
Let me go to Manage Order.

64
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:47,600
And Customer, let me go there and click Cancel Order.

65
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:52,230
Perfect. Order canceled.

66
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:54,360
Then, let me go to Stripe

67
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:58,590
and see if a refund request actually came through.

68
00:03:58,590 --> 00:04:02,040
We will go to Payments here, and perfect.

69
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:04,710
You can see refund has been initiated.

70
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:09,570
And Payment Intent, if you notice, ends in SAD,

71
00:04:09,570 --> 00:04:12,423
and that is what we have right here.

72
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:18,089
So canceling an order is working as expected,

73
00:04:18,089 --> 00:04:22,233
and we are giving them a refund if the payment was made.

